  "text": "The shape of the model index set L arising from the order ideal property is important. It is exactly the shape which, in the literature has been called variously: \"staircase models\", \"hierarchical models\", \"wellformulated models\", or \"marginality condition\", see [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . It can be be seen easily from the fact that the multi-index terms given by L are the complement in the non-negative integer orthant of those given by the monomials in the monomial ideal of leading terms: the complement of a union of orthants has the staircase property.",
